"Assembly Member, include navigation and civil aviation, financial services, "
"telecommunications, postal services, the national minimum wage, defence, "
"immigration, taxation, and elections."
msgstr ""

#: templates/website/yourrep/mp.html:3
msgid ""
"You’ll often hear people say, \"I’m going to write to my MP\" when something "
"upsets them. It’s a wide-held belief that MPs are there to solve every type "
"of problem.\n"
"\n"
"In fact, Parliament and central government are only responsible for certain "
"matters. Those are the issues with which your MP can help. If your problem "
"does not fall within one of the following areas, then you should consider "
"contacting one of your other representatives. \n"
"\n"
"<strong> MPs can help you with matters such as:</strong>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"    <li><strong>Tax problems</strong> involving HM Revenue &amp; Customs\n"
"        (but not issues with, for example, the council tax, which is "
"administered by your local authority).</li>\n"
"    <li>Problems with <strong>hospitals and the NHS</strong>, if you are in "
"England. The Scottish\n"
"        and Welsh Parliaments are responsible for health matters in Scotland "
"and Wales respectively.</li>\n"
"    <li>Problems with <strong>benefits, pensions and national insurance</"
"strong> (but not problems with the social services department of your local "
"authority).</li>\n"
"    <li>Issues dealt with by the Home Office, such as <strong>immigration</"
"strong>.</li>\n"
"    <li>In England, matters such as <strong>school closures and grants</"
"strong> (but not day to day\n"
"        problems involving schools, which are overseen by their governors "
"and your local\n"
"        education authority). In Scotland and Wales the devolved "
"Parliaments\n"
"        are responsible for education issues.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"\n"
"Your MP <strong>cannot</strong> help you in private disputes with other "
"<strong>individuals</strong> or with <strong>companies</strong> who have "
"sold you faulty goods, nor, for example, can they interfere with decisions "
"made by <strong>courts</strong>.\n"
"\n"
"<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-"
"information-office/fymp/yaympenglish.pdf\">You and Your MP</a> [PDF],\n"
"a factsheet produced by Parliament, has more information about what your MP "
"can\n"
"do for you."
msgstr ""

#: templates/website/yourrep/msp.html:3
msgid ""
"MSPs deal with any issues for which the Scottish Parliament is responsible. "
"They include:\n"
"\n"
"<ul>\n"
"    <li>health</li>\n"
"    <li>education and training</li>\n"
"    <li>local government</li>\n"
"    <li>social work</li>\n"
"    <li>housing</li>\n"
"    <li>planning</li>\n"
"    <li>tourism, economic development and financial assistance to industry</"
"li>\n"
"    <li>some aspects of transport, including the Scottish road network, bus "
"policy and ports and harbours</li>\n"
"    <li>law and home affairs, including most aspects of criminal and civil "
"law, the prosecution system and the courts</li>\n"
"    <li>police and fire services</li>\n"
"    <li>environment</li>\n"
"    <li>natural and built heritage</li>\n"
"    <li>agriculture, forestry and fishing</li>\n"
"    <li>sport and the arts</li>\n"
"    <li>statistics, public registers and records</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"\n"
"For constituency matters, you can approach any one of the MSPs who represent "
"you. Do not contact more than one MSP on a constituency matter, as this will "
"cause potential delays. \n"
"Only contact all your regional MSPs about issues that apply to all of them "
"&ndash; for example, if you wish them to cast a particular vote in the "
"Scottish Parliament."
msgstr ""

#: templates/website/yourrep/mtw.html:1
msgid ""
"The Metropolitan District Council is responsible for all aspects of\n"
"<strong>local services and policy</strong>, including\n"
"<strong>planning</strong>, <strong>transport</strong>, <strong>roads</"
"strong>\n"
"(except trunk roads and motorways), public rights of way,\n"
"<strong>education</strong>, <strong>social services</strong> and\n"
"<strong>libraries</strong>."
msgstr ""

